# Build-context exclusions for entity-workbench-go/avalonia/Containerfile.
#
# WHY THIS FILE LIVES HERE: podman reads .containerignore from the
# build context root only. The avalonia Containerfile uses this
# directory (the parent of all sibling entity-* repos) as its context,
# so the ignore file must live here too.

# `make -C entity-workbench-go/avalonia extract` writes here, which
# sits *inside* the COPY'd subtree. Without this exclusion, every
# extract mutates the workbench-go subtree, invalidating the
# `COPY entity-workbench-go` layer on the next build and re-running
# the entire Go + dotnet pipeline from scratch. With this exclusion,
# successive `make up` runs are fully cache-hit.
entity-workbench-go/avalonia/dist-native/

# .git directories aren't needed for the build and are large + churny.
# Excluding them shrinks the context tarball and stabilizes the
# COPY layer hash against unrelated git activity.
**/.git/
